children.subject: I believe Dan Garcia said it would be, and that Victor Huang would be teaching it like last summer.

Dear Students; 

 
Please note that we WILL now be offering CS 375 in summer 2015. It is possible that it will not appear on the schedule until February, but it will be added. First-time CS GSIs who intended to apply for summer GSI positions now have an option to take CS 375 now (spring) or in summer.
 
We have not yet made a final decision on if we will offer EE 375 during summer 2015.  We will let you know once this decision has been finalized. If EE 375 is not offered, then first-time GSIs for EE courses have an option to take EE 375 this semester or CS 375 during summer. 
 
Thanks,
Sarah

Dear Students- 

Please note that EE/CS 375 (Teaching Techniques) will not be available in Summer 2015. If you're thinking about TAing during the summer term, and you have not already taken the 375 course, you MUST take it during Spring 15.  EE/CS 375 is a requirement to be eligible to teach. 

If you have any questions, please email me at svannostrand@eecs.berkeley.edu.


Thanks,

Sarah
